[[File:Capa,_Death_of_a_Loyalist_Soldier.jpg|thumb]]
'''倒下的士兵'''（{{lang-en|'''The Falling Soldier'''}}，{{lang-es|'''Muerte de un miliciano'''}}）是一张由[[罗伯特·卡帕|罗伯特·卡帕]]拍摄的照片，據稱攝於1936年9月5日星期六，內容是[[西班牙内战|西班牙内战]]时期的一位共和政府派{{tsl|en|Iberian Federation of Libertarian Youth||伊比利亚自由意志青年联合会}}（FIJL）士兵之死。这名士兵后来被認為是[[无政府主义者|无政府主义者]]{{tsl|en|Federico Borrell García||费德里科·博雷利·加西亚}}，西班牙政府的檔案館保存了他在木里亞諾山（Cerro Muriano）陣亡的日期記錄。[[長槍黨|長槍黨]]從一開始就指出照片為擺拍<ref group="注">指被拍摄对象是刻意为摄影师摆出造型拍摄的，而非真实自然状态下的抓拍。</ref>作品。自二十世纪七十年代以後，人們針對攝影地點、相片主角，以及發現同時間地點所拍攝的其他相片，以及對於本相片是否為真正的[[纪实摄影|纪实影像]]提出了懷疑。<ref>{{cite news |authorlink= |coauthors= |title=Robert Capa 'faked' war photo new evidence produced |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/spain/3042469/Robert-Capa-faked-war-photo-new-evidence-produced.html |quote=Looking at the photos it is clear that it is not the heat of battle. It is likely the soldiers were carrying out an exercise either for Capa or themselves. |work=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Telegraph]] |date=September 21, 2008 |accessdate=2009-07-26 |location=London |first=Alastair |last=Jamieson |archive-date=2009-06-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090605173542/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/spain/3042469/Robert-Capa-faked-war-photo-new-evidence-produced.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

最近的研究指出照片並非為戰役現場實況拍攝（可能是摆拍而非纪实），指其並非摄于{{tsl|es|Cerro Muriano||木里亚诺山}}战役處，而是在大约30英里外的[[Espejo_(Córdoba)|埃斯佩霍]]。<ref>{{cite news |first= |last= |authorlink= |coauthors= |title=What Spain Sees in Robert Capa's Civil War Photo |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-1201116/How-Capas-camera-does-lie-The-photographic-proof-iconic-Falling-Soldier-image-staged.html |quote=While the new findings clearly establish where the famous shot was taken, not everyone believes they suggest it was a fraud. "The evidence certainly changes the photograph's location from Cerro Muriano to Espejo — there's no longer any question about that," says Cynthia Young, a curator at the International Center of Photography in charge of the Robert Capa and Cornell Capa Archive and one of the exhibition's organizers. |work=[[Time_magazine|Time magazine]] |date=July 25, 2009 |accessdate=2009-07-26 |archive-date=2020-08-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200806194334/https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-1201116/How-Capas-camera-does-lie-The-photographic-proof-iconic-Falling-Soldier-image-staged.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><!-- more links: <ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/art/news/shot-down--capas-classic-image-of-war-1754405.html | work=The Independent | location=London | title=Shot down - Capa's classic image of war | first=Elizabeth | last=Nash | date=July 21, 2009 | accessdate=March 27, 2010}}</ref><ref>[http://www.editorandpublisher.com/eandp/news/article_display.jsp?vnu_content_id=1003995503]</ref>
