==历史背景==
[[File:Freedom_is_not_Free.JPG|thumb]]。]]
{{main|西班牙内战}}
西班牙內戰是由弗朗哥領導，受境外法西斯勢力支持的西班牙國民軍，對抗左派共和政府的戰爭。政府徵召民兵組建了西班牙共和軍來應對戰事。這張照片在當時發表於雜誌上時，被認為是一名共和軍士兵賭上性命與敵人作戰，最終中彈倒地的一瞬間。 <!--[[ス_ペイン内戦|ス ペイン内戦]]（[[スペイン戦争|スペイン戦争]]） は、左派の共和国政府に対して、ナチスなどが支援した反乱軍が起こした戦争で、それに対して義勇兵などが集まって共和国軍として戦ったものであるが、この 「崩れ落ちる兵士」は、共和国政府側の兵士が命を賭けて反乱軍と戦っている最中に銃弾で倒れたところを写したものだ、と、この写真が雑誌で公表された当時 から信じられ、反ファシズムのシンボルのように扱われた写真であり、22歳の無名の青年だったキャパを一躍有名にした写真である。-->照片成為世界[[反法西斯|反法西斯]]的象徵，沒沒無名的22歲攝影家[[安德鲁·弗里德曼|安德鲁·弗里德曼]]（羅伯特·卡帕的原名）因此一舉成名。

卡帕關於木里亞諾山的民兵的照片，最早發表於1936年9月23日出版的法國雜誌《視》上 ，照片的全稱是《效忠共和國民兵的死亡瞬間，木里亞諾山，1936年9月5日》（{{lang|en|Loyalist Militiaman at the Moment of Death, Cerro Muriano, September 5, 1936}}）<ref name="nhk_document">NHK、『{{tsl|ja|沢木耕太郎 推理ドキュメント 運命の一枚〜“戦場”写真 最大の謎に挑む〜}}』（2013年2月3日放映）</ref>。同期發表的照片中包括兩張被擊中民兵的照片，在雜誌同一頁的下方登載了另一張在同一個地點拍攝的、顯示倒下進一步動作的照片，據稱為同一作者所拍攝。一天之後，同一個地區拍攝的其他照片也被發表在雜誌《Regards》上。在美國，《倒下的士兵》在1937年7月12日被當時已經擁有一百萬份的發行量的 《[[生活_(雜誌)|生活]]》雜誌刊載。當時《生活》僅刊登了一張照片，照片配有粗體字標題“DEATH IN SPAIN : THE CIVIL WAR HAS TAKEN 500,000 LIVES IN ONE YEAR"（死亡在西班牙：內戰一年已奪去五十萬條生命）。照片底下附有小號字體的文字說明"ROBERT CAPA'S CAMERA CATCHES A SPANISH SOLDIER THE INSTANT HE IS DROPPED BY A BULLET THROUGH THE HEAD"（羅伯特·卡帕的鏡頭捕捉到一位西班牙士兵頭部中彈倒下的瞬間）。<!--この時には、一枚のみが掲載された。その写真のタイトルは「DEATH IN SPAIN : THE CIVIL WAR HAS TAKEN 500,000 LIVES IN ONE YEAR」とボールド（太文字）で書かれていた。写真下のキャプションには小さな活字で「ROBERT CAPA'S CAMERA CATCHES A SPANISH SOLDIER THE INSTANT HE IS DROPPED BY A BULLET THROUGH THE HEAD（キャパのカメラは兵士の頭が銃で撃ち抜かれる瞬間をとらえた）」との文章が添えられていた--><ref name="nhk_document"/><ref group="注">『ロバート・キャパ写真集 Photographs』p257 の沢木耕太郎解説では「ロバート・キャパのカメラが、コルドバで一人のスペイン共和国軍兵士が頭部を弾丸で貫通され倒れる瞬間をとらえた」と訳している。 また、同書解説内で「この写真は演じられたものであろう」と評している。</ref>。

== 真伪之争 ==
自1975年以來有不少人質疑照片拍攝時的真偽<ref>[[Phillip_Knightley|Phillip Knightley]] (1975). ''The First Casualty: From the Crimea to Vietnam; The War Correspondent as Hero, Propagandist, and Myth Maker''. New York: Harcourt, Brace</ref>，但仍有一些作家，如卡帕的传记作者理查德·惠藍（Richard Whelan），始终坚信的照片的真实性<ref>Richard Whelan (2002).[http://www.pbs.org/wnet/americanmasters/database/capa_r.html Proving that Robert Capa's "Falling Soldier" is genuine: A detective story] {{Wayback|url=http://www.pbs.org/wnet/americanmasters/database/capa_r.html |date=20070321161406 }}, [[American_Masters|American Masters]].</ref>。不過在西班牙內戰期間攝影記者們受到種種限制（例如不准記者到前線；即便到了前線也會受到限制），攝影記者常要求士兵們擺出戰鬥的樣子以拍攝照片。<ref name="Vaill excerpt">{{Cite web | last = Vaill | first = Amanda | date = 22 April 2014 | title = Did Robert Capa Fake 'Falling Soldier'? | url = https://foreignpolicy.com/2014/04/22/did-robert-capa-fake-falling-soldier/ | website = foreignpolicy.com | accessdate = 22 August 2015 | archive-date = 2020-12-09 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201209164510/https://foreignpolicy.com/2014/04/22/did-robert-capa-fake-falling-soldier/ | dead-url = no }}</ref> 雖然據稱照片拍攝地點是在木里亞諾山的戰場 ，但近年研究顯示拍攝地點是大約50公里外，名為[[Espejo_(Córdoba)|埃斯佩霍]]的小鎮。<ref>{{cite news |title=What Spain Sees in Robert Capa's Civil War Photo |url=http://content.time.com/time/world/article/0,8599,1912110,00.html |quote=While the new findings clearly establish where the famous shot was taken, not everyone believes they suggest it was a fraud. "The evidence certainly changes the photograph's location from Cerro Muriano to Espejo — there's no longer any question about that," says Cynthia Young, a curator at the International Center of Photography in charge of the Robert Capa and Cornell Capa Archive and one of the exhibition's organizers, who goes on to add, "But I don't see how one goes from 'new location' to 'fake photo' — it's a lot more complicated than that. Capa never said the photo was taken at Cerra Muriano — not once, not anywhere." |work=[[Time_magazine|Time magazine]] |date=July 25, 2009 |accessdate=2009-07-26 |archive-date=2021-03-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210317192505/http://content.time.com/time/world/article/0,8599,1912110,00.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>
<!-- more links: <ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/art/news/shot-down--capas-classic-image-of-war-1754405.html | work=The Independent | location=London | title=Shot down - Capa's classic image of war | first=Elizabeth | last=Nash | date=July 21, 2009 | accessdate=March 27, 2010}}</ref><ref>[http://www.editorandpublisher.com/eandp/news/article_display.jsp?vnu_content_id=1003995503]</ref><ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/blogs/photoblog/2009/07/the_whole_story.html</ref>-->

2007年纪录片《冰山的阴影》（{{tsl|en|La sombra del iceberg}}）声称该照片系摆拍，且照片上的主角並不是博雷利<ref>{{Cite web|title=''Autopsia al miliciano de Robert Capa''|url=http://www.elmundo.es/elmundo/2008/02/02/valencia/1201946356.html|accessdate=2013-09-29|dead-url=no|archive-date=2020-09-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200922193110/https://www.elmundo.es/elmundo/2008/02/02/valencia/1201946356.html}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.elmundo.es/elmundo/2008/02/02/valencia/1201946356.html |title=Autopsia al miliciano de Robert Capa |publisher=elmundo.es |accessdate=2013-10-20 |archive-date=2020-09-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200922193110/https://www.elmundo.es/elmundo/2008/02/02/valencia/1201946356.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。荷西·曼紐爾·蘇斯培里圭（José Manuel Susperregui）於 2009 所出版的書籍「相片的陰影」（ ''Sombras de la Fotografía，''"Shadows of Photography"），認為相片並非在木里亚诺山拍攝。他分析了在該相片前後所拍攝的其他相片的背景，發現遠處有山。他將相片以電子郵件寄給Córdoba附近的幾個小鎮的圖書館員與歷史學家，詢問是否有人認出其中地景。結果在西班牙小鎮[[Espejo_(Córdoba)|埃斯佩霍]]有人回應確認。但[[Espejo_(Córdoba)|埃斯佩霍]]距離卡帕當時所在的戰線數十英里之遠，蘇斯培里圭據此認為本相片與其他同系列的相片，原先被認為是在前線所攝，都是擺拍的。<ref>{{Cite book | last = Susperregui | first = José Manuel | title = Sombras de la Fotografía: Los Enigmas Desvelados de Nicolasa Ugartemendia, Muerte de un Miliciano, la Aldea Española, el Lute | publisher = Universidad del Pais Vasco | year = 2008 | isbn = 978-84-9860-230-2}}</ref>

蘇斯培里圭也提出了一般論點中的幾個不合之處，例如卡帕指出主角是被一波機槍子彈－－而非狙擊手的子彈－－射殺。卡帕對於視角與拍攝時的技術參數，也沒有一致的說法。<ref>{{Cite news | last = Rohter | first = Larry | title = New Doubts Raised Over Famous War Photo | newspaper = New York Times | date = 17 August 2009 | url = https://www.nytimes.com/2009/08/18/arts/design/18capa.html?ref=international_center_of_photography | accessdate = 2021-04-01 | archive-date = 2020-07-27 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200727064347/https://www.nytimes.com/2009/08/18/arts/design/18capa.html?ref=international_center_of_photography | dead-url = no }}</ref> 西班牙的報紙（包括巴塞隆納的 ''El Periódico de Catalunya）''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rawstory.com/news/afp/Iconic_Capa_war_photo_was_staged_ne_07172009.html |title=The Raw Story | Iconic Capa war photo was staged: newspaper |publisher=Web.archive.org |accessdate=2013-10-20 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090720232147/http://rawstory.com/news/afp/Iconic_Capa_war_photo_was_staged_ne_07172009.html |archive-date=July 20, 2009 }}</ref>派出記者到[[Espejo_(Córdoba)|埃斯佩霍]]，結果拍到的相片中，天際線與背景跟卡帕的作品很相近。

國際攝影中心（International Center of Phtography）的主席威利斯·E·哈次洪（Willis E. Hartshorn）則反對本照片是擺拍的說法。他認為相片中的士兵是在準備擺拍時被遠方狙擊者的子彈射殺。蘇斯培里圭並不認同，因為當時的戰線距離太遠，且在 Córdoba前線並未有使用狙擊手的紀錄。

對於相片中的主角身分也有存疑。雖然一般認為主角是{{tsl|en|Federico Borrell García||费德里科·博雷利·加西亚}}，但他是在木里亞諾山戰場，躲在樹後尋求掩護時陣亡的。此外除了本相片實際拍攝地點不明外，{{tsl|en|Federico Borrell García||费德里科·博雷利·加西亚}}的外表與影中人也不是很相像。<ref>{{cite web | last = Faber | first = Sebastiaan | title = Truth in the Making: The Never-Ending Saga of Capa’s Falling Soldier | publisher = The Volunteer | date = 17 March 2010 | url = http://www.albavolunteer.org/2010/03/truth-in-the-making-the-never-ending-saga-of-capas-falling-soldier/ | access-date = 2021-04-01 | archive-date = 2021-04-22 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210422142819/https://albavolunteer.org/2010/03/truth-in-the-making-the-never-ending-saga-of-capas-falling-soldier/ | dead-url = no }}</ref>



== 墨西哥手提箱（"Mexican Suitcase"）裡的相片 ==
卡帕與其他兩位攝影家（Gerda Taro、David Seymour）的三箱負片作品在2007年被寄到紐約的國際攝影中心，被稱為「墨西哥手提箱（"Mexican Suitcase"）」<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.icp.org/exhibitions/the-mexican-suitcase-traveling-exhibition |title=The Mexican Suitcase: Rediscovered Spanish Civil War Negatives by Capa, Chim, and Taro |date=16 May 2016 |work=[[International_Center_of_Photography|International Center of Photography]] |access-date=14 September 2017 |archive-date=2021-02-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210211201100/https://www.icp.org/exhibitions/the-mexican-suitcase-traveling-exhibition |dead-url=no }}</ref> 其中包含了卡帕的數百張負片，在戰爭結束時帶到墨西哥。這些相片現存於國際攝影中心的卡帕檔案中。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/01/27/arts/design/27kenn.html |title=The Capa Cache |newspaper=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]] |access-date=19 October 2013 |first=Randy |last=Kennedy |date=27 January 2008 |publisher=[[The_New_York_Times_Company|The New York Times Company]] |page=AR1 |archive-date=2021-05-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210502135537/https://www.nytimes.com/2008/01/27/arts/design/27kenn.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

但其中並沒有本片的原始負片。但在2008年巡迴展示的數百張其他相片中，有與本相片同時同地拍攝的作品，分析其中的地景以後，認為不論本相片是實況或是擺拍，拍攝地點就是埃斯佩霍。<ref>{{Cite web |title=This Is War! Robert Capa at Work : Gerda Taro : On the Subject of War |url=http://www.barbican.org.uk/artgallery/event-detail.asp?ID=8029 |work=[[Barbican_Art_Gallery|Barbican Art Gallery]] |access-date=22 August 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150627155423/http://www.barbican.org.uk/artgallery/event-detail.asp?ID=8029 |archive-date=27 June 2015 |date=25 January 2009 |publisher=[[City_of_London_Corporation|City of London Corporation]]}}</ref>

從某種角度講，這些發現也為卡帕開脫了罪責。之前有一些作家認為卡帕可能需要為該民兵的死亡負責－－當民兵被狙擊手槍殺時，似乎正準備為卡帕擺姿勢。 <ref>{{cite news |author=[[Isabel_Hilton|Isabel Hilton]] |coauthors= |title=The camera never lies. But photographers can and do |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/commentisfree/2008/sep/27/photography.pressandpublishing |quote=Capa was a great photographer but he was not averse to faking. In 1937 he fabricated footage for the March of Time newsreel series. He told the Life photographer, Hansel Mieth, that the Borrell picture had been taken when the militiamen were fooling around, not in the heat of battle as had been believed. She added that Capa seemed upset and said little more except that it "haunted him badly". ... As Borrell stood to pose for Capa, he was cut down by a rebel bullet. |work=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]] |date=September 27, 2008 |accessdate=2009-07-26 |location=London |archive-date=2012-11-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121114030207/http://www.guardian.co.uk/commentisfree/2008/sep/27/photography.pressandpublishing |dead-url=no }}</ref>

